This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face discrimination systems and deep convolutional neural networks. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as these fields are closely related to computer vision. Additionally, it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as face recognition is often used in multimedia applications. Finally, it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as the method involves the use of neural networks.
